{
  "texts": [
    "As shown in Table VI, GC methods amplify the graph data bias to varying degrees.",
    "Gradient matching and distribution matching not only achieve the lowest node classification accuracy but also exhibit the most pronounced bias.",
    "More advanced optimization strategies, i.e., KRR and trajectory matching, can effectively reduce this bias while preserving predictive performance.",
    "Robustness.",
    "We evaluate the robustness of GC methods to structural noise, which involves randomly adding and removing edges."
  ]
}